-- Pirelli signs MOU with Egypt for plant expansion
-- 
-- Tue Nov 25, 2014 06:00AM EST
-- None



MILAN, Nov 25 (Reuters) - Italian tyremaker Pirelli <PECI.MI> said on Tuesday it had signed a memorandum of understanding with Egyptian authorities for a possible expansion of a tyre plant in Alexandria.

According to the MOU, Alexandria Tire Co. (Atco), which is more than 90 percent controlled by Pirelli and produces radial truck tyres, would invest around $107 million in the expansion.